<Link id="l00492" /><CodeLine lineNumber="492"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This pass only makes sense when the underlying chip has floating point but</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00493" /><CodeLine lineNumber="493"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// we are compiling as mips16.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00494" /><CodeLine lineNumber="494"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For all mips16 functions (that are not stubs we have already generated), or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00495" /><CodeLine lineNumber="495"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// declared via attributes as nomips16, we must:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00496" /><CodeLine lineNumber="496"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    1) fixup all returns of float, double, single and double complex</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00497" /><CodeLine lineNumber="497"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       by calling a helper function before the actual return.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00498" /><CodeLine lineNumber="498"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    2) generate helper functions (stubs) that can be called by mips32</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00499" /><CodeLine lineNumber="499"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       functions that will move parameters passed normally passed in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00500" /><CodeLine lineNumber="500"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       floating point</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00501" /><CodeLine lineNumber="501"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       registers the soft float equivalents.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00502" /><CodeLine lineNumber="502"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    3) in the case of static relocation, generate helper functions so that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00503" /><CodeLine lineNumber="503"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       mips16 functions can call extern functions of unknown type (mips16 or</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00504" /><CodeLine lineNumber="504"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       mips32).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00505" /><CodeLine lineNumber="505"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    4) TBD. For pic, calls to extern functions of unknown type are handled by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00506" /><CodeLine lineNumber="506"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       predefined helper functions in libc but this work is currently done</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00507" /><CodeLine lineNumber="507"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//       during call lowering but it should be moved here in the future.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00508" /><CodeLine lineNumber="508" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mips16hardfloat-cpp-/mips16hardfloat/#afe38556e5426f0e8a8c0c06bfa91769b"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-mips16hardfloat-cpp-/mips16hardfloat/#afe38556e5426f0e8a8c0c06bfa91769b">Mips16HardFloat::runOnModule</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/module">Module</a> &amp;M) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
